# ============================================
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES:
# ============================================
# 1. Never commit .env files with real credentials
# 2. Never commit private keys or certificates
# 3. Never commit real credentials.json files
# 4. Never commit database files
# 5. Use .env.example as template instead
# 6. Use environment variables for sensitive data
# 7. Review .gitignore before each commit
# 8. Use git-secrets to prevent credential leaks
# 9. Setup branch protection rules
# 10. Enable code scanning and dependency checks

